food, very good amenities and swimming pool.</p>\\n<blockquote>\\n<p class=\\\"alert alert-error\\\"><strong>We recommend that volunteers arrive one to two nights before their chosen program starts, and their first night accommodation and meals at the travellers hostel is covered by us. You will be accompanied there by one of our staff members.</strong></p>\\n</blockquote>\\n<p>Your transfers from and back to the airport are covered in your program fees, and you will be travelling with one of our staff members on both occasions. <br /> <br /> For the duration of your program, your accommodation, breakfast and dinner at your home stay is covered in the program fee.</p>\\n<blockquote>\\n<p class=\\\"alert alert-error\\\"><strong>Orientation will take place at the traveller\'s hostel in the morning of the first and third Mondays of each month.</strong><br /> <br /><strong> Orientation is extremely important and each volunteer must attend.</strong><br /> <br /><strong> Here you will be introduced to Kenya, its national language Swahili.</strong><br /> <br /><strong> It helps to know some basics, safety rules, and an introduction to your program placement and home stay.</strong><br /> <br /><strong> Our staff will also introduce you to some ideas for your weekend fun, and there is plenty of fun to be had in Kenya. Kenya has some of the best National parks, wild life, and coast line on the planet.</strong></p>\\n</blockquote>\\n</div>\",\"alignment\":\"\",\"text_fontsize\":\"\",\"text_lineheight\":\"\",\"text_fontweight\":\"\",\"dropcap\":0,\"class\":\"\",\"global_background_type\":\"none\",\"global_background_gradient\":{\"color\":\"#00c6fb\",\"color2\":\"#005bea\",\"deg\":\"45\",\"type\":\"linear\"},\"global_background_repeat\":\"no-repeat\",\"global_background_size\":\"cover\",\"global_background_attachment\":\"inherit\",\"global_background_position\":\"50% 50%\",\"global_use_overlay\":0,\"global_overlay_type\":\"overlay_none\",\"global_gradient_overlay\":{\"color\":\"