0,\"global_border_width\":\"\",\"global_border_radius\":0,\"global_margin\":{\"md\":\"0px 0px 30px 0px\",\"sm\":\"0px 0px 20px 0px\",\"xs\":\"0px 0px 10px 0px\"},\"global_padding\":{\"md\":\"   \",\"sm\":\"   \",\"xs\":\"   \"},\"global_boxshadow\":\"0 0 0 0 #ffffff\",\"global_use_animation\":0,\"global_animationduration\":\"300\",\"global_animationdelay\":\"0\",\"global_custom_css\":\"\",\"global_custom_position\":0,\"global_seclect_position\":\"relative\",\"global_addon_position_left\":{\"unit\":\"px\"},\"global_addon_position_top\":{\"unit\":\"px\"},\"use_global_width\":0,\"hidden_md\":0,\"hidden_sm\":0,\"hidden_xs\":0,\"acl\":\"\",\"while_scroll_view\":[{\"enable_while_scroll_view\":0,\"on_scroll_actions\":[{\"id\":\"b3fdc1c1e6bfde5942ea\",\"index\":0,\"keyframe\":0,\"name\":\"move\",\"property\":{\"x\":\"0\",\"y\":\"-100\",\"z\":\"0\"},\"range\":{\"max\":500,\"min\":-500,\"stop\":1},\"single\":true,\"title\":\"Move\"},{\"id\":\"936e0225e6dc8edfba7d\",\"index\":1,\"keyframe\":100,\"name\":\"move\",\"property\":{\"x\":0,\"y\":0,\"z\":0},\"range\":{\"max\":500,\"min\":-500,\"stop\":1},\"single\":true,\"title\":\"Move\"}],\"transition_origin_x\":\"center\",\"transition_origin_y\":\"center\",\"enable_tablet\":0,\"enable_mobile\":0}],\"mouse_movement\":[{\"enable_tilt_effect\":0,\"mouse_tilt_direction\":\"direct\",\"mouse_tilt_speed\":\"1\",\"mouse_tilt_max\":\"15\",\"enable_tablet\":0,\"enable_mobile\":0}]}},{\"id\":1573694509499,\"name\":\"text_block\",\"visibility\":true,\"settings\":{\"admin_label\":\"\",\"title\":\"\",\"heading_selector\":\"h3\",\"title_fontsize\":\"\",\"title_lineheight\":\"\",\"title_letterspace\":\"0\",\"text\":\"<div>\\n<p><strong>Uganda</strong> - home of the great Lake Victoria, source of the truly amazing Nile River, and the further amazing Murchison Falls National Park. <br /> <br /> Uganda has some of the friendliest &amp; loving communities you will ever meet.</p>\\n<h2><strong>Location and duration</strong></h2>\\n<p>Our Ugandan programs are based in and around the Jinja District, which is close to the great Lake Victoria and the amazing Nile river. With these two great natural wonders there is lots to see and do around Jinja Town. <br /> <br /> The town of Jinja is approximately 80 Km from the capital city Kampala, and Kampala is about 40Km from Uganda’s International airport, Entebbe. The Intake for the volunteer programs happen Twice per month, the first weekend and the third weekend of every month. Thus giving us the pleasure to build groups so that you have the opportunity to meet other volunteers from all around the world. <br /> <br /> All the Volunteer In Africa programs require a commitment from the volunteers for at least two weeks, this helps the volunteer in africa staff help you make a real difference in your community and your self, along with your 25% of fees donated to your chosen project leaving behind a lot more than just foot prints.</p>\\n<blockquote>\\n<p class=\\\"alert alert-error\\\">The maximum Length of stay for our volunteers is 20 weeks.</p>\\n</blockquote>\\n<h2><strong>Projects</strong></h2>\\n<h3><strong>Teaching</strong></h3>\\n<p>The schools that Volunteer In Africa partner with are mostly independent schools with no government funding. These schools are heavily under resourced and our aim is to increase opportunities for Ugandan students from disadvantaged backgrounds to receive a quality education. You will see that there are so many projects in our school environments that your 25% donation can go to. <br /> <br /> Our experiences have told us that the teaching program is extremely rewarding for all involved. The program coordinators are always on hand to support the volunteers in their teaching roll, there fore no experience is necessary. <br /> <br /> The Teaching programs do operate during Ugandan official school holidays because our schools are all independently owned and operated. Some children still come to school for extra classes, some come just to hang out, and some come for the food program’s. Our schools are always operating.</p>\\n<h3><strong>Sports Education</strong></h3>\\n<p>This program relies on you the volunteer to organize the sports you want to do with your community leaders. You will need to set training programs, games and tournaments, the sporting program brings the whole community together and quiet often friends and families get involved. Most of Volunteer in Africa’s communities that we work with do not have sporting goods and its up to you the volunteer to take with you what you will need. What might be old scratched equipment to you, is new, highly desirable and sort after with the communities you will be working with. <br /> <br /> Ugandans absolutely love soccer and will play it all day long if allowed. However Uganda is a very sporty nation and there are a lot of sponsored sporting events on all the time around the country, everything from basketball, netball, cricket, Hockey, athletics and rugby are on all the time, therefor the children know and are good at lots of sports. Depending on your placement you will be required to help out in the classrooms during the morning, then run the sporting program’s in the afternoon.</p>\\n<h3><strong>Special Needs Care</strong></h3>\\n<p>The communities that Volunteer in Africa works with for Special needs programs in Uganda are very poor and many people still live in traditional mud huts or very basic brick structures without running water or electricity. Disabled children are probably the most marginalized children in Africa due to the social stigma surrounding disability together with a lack of services to help them. In the area we operate there are not any other disability organizations and there are children living in terrible situations. <br /> <br /> The Volunteer in Africa program coordinators along with the special needs centers staff are there to help and guide you through this program. Some of the therapy clinics we work with have their own physiotherapist and are some of the most inspirational people you will ever meet. No experience is necessary for this program just the desire to be there and help out the most disenfranchised people in Uganda is greatly appreciated and desperately needed. If you have a therapy, social care, or medical background, this is a bonus. <br /> <br /> In this program the aim is to increase the access for care and education for Ugandans with special needs. The 25% of your program fees for the special needs care can be used in so many ways, from building wheel chairs, crutches, medication, physiotherapy, you will have no trouble finding a place for your 25% to go. We have found that this is one of the most rewarding programs we offer.</p>\\n<h3><strong>Childcare / Orphanage Work</strong></h3>\\n<p>The Volunteer In Africa’s partners who we work with in these fields are some of the most inspirational people you will ever meet. <br /> <br /> Uganda has a lot of children that are homeless for way to many reasons. The AIDS epidemic of the 1990”s and early 2000”s is just one circumstance, in many a case its as simple as the family cant afford to feed their child so they end up on the streets trying to fend for them selves. The Childcare centres that we partner with work constantly with government officials to identify the children that need a home the most and do their best to provide it. <br /> <br /> The duties of the volunteers in this program range from educational schooling to Teaching life skills .If your passionate about children getting the basic building blocks of life then this is a fantastic program for you. Its also a program where your 25% can be used in so many ways, most of the time our childcare and orphanage partners rely soly on donations. All children are not created equal, but all children deserve the right to the basic building blocks of life.</p>\\n<h3><strong>Construction and Renovation</strong></h3>\\n<p>If you love the outdoors and team comradely then you will love the Ugandan construction program. You will work along with the Volunteer In Africa’s program coordinators and the local builders, therefor there is no experience necessary, If you are an experienced laborer or you have a skilled trade then please let us know. The building program does not run all year round as it depends on what projects are running at the time. <br /> <br /> The focus of the building Program is to help develop the independent schools, children center’s, and special needs facilities and equipment. The volunteers duties range from painting, brick laying, roofing, and building wheelchairs just to name a few. <br /> <br /> Many of the independent schools that we work with have classrooms of dirt floors and mud brick walls, the 25% of your program fees can be used while your there on the job. It may go towards a concrete floor to keep everyone out of the water when it rains, patching roofs, or new black boards, just to name a few examples, the choice is yours. If you wish to raise money with your friends and family in order to build complete new classrooms while your there or after your gone, please let us know and we will find you some projects to choose from.</p>\\n<h3><strong>Music</strong></h3>\\n<p>Ugandans absolutely love music and dancing, but playing a musical instrument is a luxury that most never get the opportunity to do. The volunteers in this program have to supply their own instruments so your limitations on what you can teach are up to you. The aim of this project is to support local children to embrace a positive form of self-expression and to let their voices and songs be heard. This project is well suited to volunteers who have a passion for music and are able to independently create and implement their own music lesson plans. <br /> <br /> As the schools that Volunteer In Africa partner with are independently owned and operated they are open during the official Ugandan school holidays. Formal classes will not be operating but there are still plenty of children around as it gives them a place to hang out, play sports, and get a meal. This is a grate time for music lessons and sometimes when the most fun and best results are achieved.</p>\\n<h3><strong>Sustainable Farming</strong></h3>\\n<p>Are you passionate about sustainable and organic farming? - we at Volunteer In Africa definitely are. The communities and organizations that we partner with are some of the most disadvantaged in Uganda and food programs are a constant financial burden. For our partner communities to not only grow their own food, but to trade and sell their products, helps them become self sufficient and goes a long way towards self fulfillment. <br /> <br /> Volunteers in this program should be prepared to get a little dirty and a little hard work. The work requirements in this program vary, you might be chipping out weeds, sowing seeds, irrigating, or if your lucky you might be there for harvest time and festivals. <br /> <br /> We are more than happy for the volunteers in this program to do some study and research while they are volunteering on how the farming program might be improved. Weather it be different products grown for better trade and or diet, or it to be with water consumption, just to name a couple, we at volunteer in Africa are more than happy to hear your ideas and maybe help implement them.</p>\\n<h3><strong>Medical Program</strong></h3>\\n<p>The medical program for both pre med and medical students will start operation October/November 2018.</p>\\n</div>\",\"alignment\":\"\",\"text_fontsize\":\"\",\"text_lineheight\":\"\",\"text_fontweight\":\"\",\"dropcap\":0,\"class\":\"\",\"global_background_type\":\"none\",\"global_background_gradient\":{\"color\":\"#00c6fb\",\"color2\":\"#005bea\",\"deg\":\"45\",\"type\":\"linear\"},\"global_background_repeat\":\"no-repeat\",\"global_background_size\":\"cover\",\"global_background_attachment\":\"inherit\",\"global_background_position\":\"50% 50%\",\"global_use_o